We recommended that Management:
Discontinue the provision of cell cards to the head of offices as they were already provided with a postpaid plan. Likewise, to set a limit or should not go beyond their monthly usage to prevent disallowance in audit;

require the Municipal Treasurer to provide the Auditor with a list of offices and officials/personnel who were provided with a postpaid plan including the corresponding account number of the plan issued to them, together with the monthly billing statements or statement of accounts for the entire year to determine the reasonableness of the expenses;

discontinue the payment of telephone expenses of the DILG officer devolved therein; and

henceforth, adhere strictly with the provisions of COA Circular No. 2012-003 in order to properly safeguard the funds/resources from irregular, unnecessary, excessive or extravagant expenditures, otherwise excess amounts would be disallowed.

