We recommended that Management:

Instruct the Municipal Accountant to check the completeness of required documents before forwarding the same to the Municipal Treasurer for the processing of payment;



Observe the timely submission of accounts to the Audit Team to facilitate review thereon and avoid the imposition of sanctions pursuant to Section 39 (1) (3) of P.D. No. 1445.

We recommended that Municipal Mayor:
Instruct the Municipal Accountant and Municipal Treasurer to verify their records relative to the status of the foregoing outstanding checks which might have already been replaced;
Instruct the Municipal Accountant to make the necessary adjustments in the books and furnish a copy of the Journal Entry Voucher to the Municipal Treasurer as her basis in adjusting the cashbooks;
Instruct the Municipal Treasurer to record the reconciling items in her cashbook to reflect the correct balances; and
Instruct both the Municipal Accountant and Municipal Treasurer to reconcile their records regularly to immediately effect any adjustments affecting both records to show accurate and reliable balances.

We recommended that Municipal Mayor instruct the BAC to:
Strictly adhere with the provisions provided in the 2016 Revised IRR of 9184 by:
making sure that the BDS depicts the specific information and requirements relevant to the circumstances of each procurement activity, the applicable rules and the bid evaluation criteria that will apply to the bids such as among others the name of contract, approved budget for the contract, funding source, minimum work experience requirements for key personnel, minimum major equipment requirements, the bid security and other additional requirements specific for the procurement;
ensuring that the SLCC was supported with Certificate of Final Acceptance from the procuring entity to ensure the performance and competence of the bidder to carry out the project;
carefully verifying the computation of submitted NFCC to ensure that the bidder has the capacity to finance and implement the bid contract;
assuring that the list of contractor’s major equipment units pledged qualify with the minimum requirement specified in the BDS to determine the ability of the bidder to complete the contract; and
requiring that the Performance Security submitted are duly dated in compliance with Section 39.1 of the 2016 Revised IRR of 9184 to guarantee the faithful performance by the winning bidder of its obligations.
Submit the original copy of DOLE Approved CSHP of all infrastructure projects to the Auditor to check the authenticity of the documents;

We recommended that Management:

Instruct the contractor of the Improvement of FMR at Brgy. Rubio to apply asphalt on minor longitudinal cracks of concrete pavement to prevent them from becoming major cracks at no additional costs to the government;



Require the contractor of the Construction of Flood/River  Control at Sabangan Bato to pay liquidated damages on the 11 days delay in the completion of said project;



Require the contractors of the Construction of Flood/River Control and Improvement of Communal Irrigation System, both located at Sitio Guimod, Rubio, to comply the required backfill supported by sufficient documentation within two (2) weeks from receipt of this AOM otherwise, they shall be required to refund the amount P82,816.20 and P60,216.73, respectively; and 



Assign staff to assist the Municipal Engineer in monitoring the implementation of infrastructure projects.

